net.vivialconnect.model.number

Class Number

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.vivialconnect.model.VivialConnectResource
      • net.vivialconnect.model.number.Number
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, AssociatedNumber, AvailableNumber, INumber

    public class Number
extends VivialConnectResource
implements AssociatedNumber, AvailableNumber
    Phone numbers are the basis for sending and receiving text messages to and from your Vivial Connect account. In the course of sending text messages you must manage the phone number or set of phone numbers to use as the source and destination for your text messages.

    The API supports US phone numbers only. When searching available numbers for a phone number to provision, you can search for either Toll-Free or local (non-Toll-Free) numbers.

      • buyLocalNumber

        @Deprecated
public static AssociatedNumber buyLocalNumber(String phoneNumber,
                                                          String areaCode,
                                                          Map<String,Object> optionalParams)
                                                   throws ForbiddenAccessException,
                                                          BadRequestException,
                                                          UnauthorizedAccessException,
                                                          ServerErrorException,
                                                          ApiRequestException
        Deprecated. This method is deprecated. The API discontinued purchasing random numbers using an area code. Internally this method will look up for an available number in the API and call buyLocalNumber(String, Map) to keep existing functionality. If you provide a phone number and an area code, the phone number will be ignored. To purchase local numbers use buyLocalNumber(String, Map) instead. Purchases the specified phone number in this area code.
        Parameters:
        phoneNumber - Phone number you want to purchase in E.164 format (+country code +phone number). For US numbers, the format will be +1xxxyyyzzzz. If you specify this parameter, the area_code parameter will be ignored.
        areaCode - Three-digit US area code you want to specify for the phone number you want to purchase. The API will assign a random number within the area code. You must specify this parameter if phone_number is not specified.
        optionalParams - a map of String and Object key-value pairs used to filter results, possible values are:

        name New phone number as it is displayed to users. Default format: Friendly national format: (xxx) yyy-zzzz.

        status_text_url URL to receive message status callback requests for messages sent via the API using this associated phone number. Max. length: 256 characters. incoming_text_url URL for receiving SMS messages to the associated phone number. Max. length: 256 characters.

        incoming_text_method HTTP method used for the incoming_text_url requests. Max. length: 8 characters. Possible values: GET or POST. Default value: POST.

        incoming_text_fallback_url URL for receiving SMS messages if incoming_text_url fails. Only valid if you provide a value for the incoming_text_url parameter. Max. length: 256 characters.

        incoming_text_fallback_method HTTP method used for incoming_text_url_fallback requests. Max. length: 8 characters. Possible values: GET or POST. Default value: POST.

        Returns:
        associated number
        Throws:
        ForbiddenAccessException - if the user does not have permission to the API resource
        BadRequestException - if the request params and/or payload are not valid
        UnauthorizedAccessException - if any of the auth properties account ID, API Key and/or API secret are not valid
        ServerErrorException - if the server is unable to process the request
        ApiRequestException - if an API error occurs

      • getAssociatedNumbers

        public static List<AssociatedNumber> getAssociatedNumbers(Map<String,String> queryParams)
                                                   throws ForbiddenAccessException,
                                                          BadRequestException,
                                                          UnauthorizedAccessException,
                                                          ServerErrorException,
                                                          ApiRequestException
        Search and filter every associated number for this Account using the API.

        If no AssociatedNumber were found for this Account, the method will return an empty List

        Parameters:
        queryParams - a map of String key-value pairs used to filter results, possible values are:

        page Page number within the returned list of associated phone numbers. Default value: 1.

        limit Number of results to return per page. Default value: 50. Maximum value: 150.

        name Filters the results to include only phone numbers exactly matching the specified name.

        contains Filters the results to include only phone numbers that match a number pattern you specify. The pattern can include digits and the following wildcard characters:

        ? : matches any single digit
        * : matches zero or more digits

        Returns:
        a list of associated number
        Throws:
        ForbiddenAccessException - if the user does not have permission to the API resource
        BadRequestException - if the request params and/or payload are not valid
        UnauthorizedAccessException - if any of the auth properties account ID, API Key and/or API secret are not valid
        ServerErrorException - if the server is unable to process the request
        ApiRequestException - if an API error occurs
        See Also:
        getAssociatedNumbers()
